  })), "\n    "), "\nHow will this dead dude help me get ahead in my life?"), mdx("p", null, "In our academic pecking order, Maths and Science always figured at the top,  subjects that we had to master. History mostly figured somewhere at\nthe bottom of this list, lower than drawing, craft, value education and even Aayo Naga perhaps. Has our monumental indifference towards History\nenabled our educationists and academicians to disfigure, hell mutilate..our own history and actually get away with it?"), mdx("p", null, "Let me begin this by recalling a small conversation with a tenth grader relative of mine.\nThis is India\u2019s history from that persons point of view:"), mdx("ol", null, mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Harappans were the first people in India, and they had a fetish for building abnormally large bath-tubs."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Their asses were then kicked by the some unknown invading Aryans."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Somewhere down the line, Alexander and his badass gang of Greeks came calling."), mdx("li", {
    parentName: "ol"
  }, "Chandragupta Maurya with his adviser Chanakya, did some awesome 420giri to take over from the Greeks."), mdx("li", {
